{"title_page": "Kodi Najm", "text_new": "{{Infobox musical artist <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject_Musicians -->\n| name = Kodi Najm\n| background = non_vocal_instrumentalist\n| image = Kodi Najm musician.jpg\n| caption = \n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1989|07|29|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Tehran]], Iran\n| genre = [[post-punk revival]], [[Techno]], [[Soundtracks]],\n| instrument = [[Guitar]], [[piano]], [[bass guitar]]\n| years_active = 2005\u2013present\n| label = [[Narnack records]], [[Correspondant Records]]\n| associated_acts = [[Krystal Klear]] [[Hypernova (band)|Hypernova]], [[The Yellow Dogs]]\n| website = http://www.kodinajm.com\n}}\n'''Kodi Najm''' (born 29 July 1989) is an Iranian-American musician, composer and producer. He is best known for his film compositions and soundtrack work. Najm was the lead guitar player for the rock band Hypernova in the early 2000s.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=125780177|title=Hypernova: An Iranian Rock Band In Brooklyn|website=npr.org|accessdate=26 December 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170316162407/http://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=125780177|archivedate=16 March 2017}}</ref>\n\n== Early life and musical career ==\nKodi Najm was born in [[Tehran|Tehran, Iran]]. He left Iran when he was 17 years old and moved to the [[New York City]] where he currently resides. He has written and released 4 Ep's (Universal, Fairy Tales (''single''), Exit Strategy)  and one full-length album [[Through the Chaos]] as a member of Hypernova.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=11182793|title=Hypernova: Illegal Indie-Rock from Iran|website=npr.org|accessdate=26 December 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303183310/http://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=11182793|archivedate=3 March 2016}}</ref> Najm has also recorded and composed a heavily electronic and orchestral concept album for the motion picture ''Koyakatsi'' in early 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/jason-silva/koyakatsi-film_b_1965107.html|title=Koyakatsi : Enter the Civilization of Light With Director Ayoub Qanir|first=Jason|last=Silva|date=18 October 2012|website=huffingtonpost.com|accessdate=26 December 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160318051149/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/jason-silva/koyakatsi-film_b_1965107.html|archivedate=18 March 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Solo work==\nCorrespondant Compilation 07\n<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.residentadvisor.net/news/44531|title=Jennifer Cardini reveals seventh Correspondant compilation|date=18 November 2019|website=residentadvisor.net|}</ref>\n- 'E.V.B.T (East Village Bass tool)' with Krystal Klear\n\n\n==Filmography==\n* ''Vortex'' (2019)\n* ''Ziona'' (2017)\n*''[https://www.nowness.com/story/jon-kortajarena-clement-chabernaud-models Thirty-Six Hours]'' (short) (2016)\n* Koyakatsi OST - Koyakatsi (Motion picture by [[Ayoub Qanir]])\n* ''Vex'' (short) (2014)\n* ''Room 237'' (short) (2012)\n\n==Band Discography==\n* Hypernova - Consequences (2006)\n* Hypernova - Universal (2008)\n* Hypernova - Fairy Tales ''(single)'' (2009)\n* Hypernova -Through The Chaos (2010)\n* Hypernova - Exit Strategy (2011)\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:najm, Kodi}}\n[[Category:1989 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox musical artist <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject_Musicians -->\n| name = Kodi Najm\n| background = non_vocal_instrumentalist\n| image = Kodi Najm musician.jpg\n| caption = \n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1989|07|29|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Tehran]], Iran\n| genre = [[post-punk revival]], [[Techno]], [[Soundtracks]],\n| instrument = [[Guitar]], [[piano]], [[bass guitar]]\n| years_active = 2005\u2013present\n| label = [[Narnack records]], [[Correspondant Records]]\n| associated_acts = [[Krystal Klear]] [[Hypernova (band)|Hypernova]], [[The Yellow Dogs]]\n| website = http://www.kodinajm.com\n}}\n'''Kodi Najm''' (born 29 July 1989) is an Iranian-American musician, composer and producer. He is best known for his film compositions and soundtrack work. Najm was the lead guitar player for the rock band Hypernova in the early 2000s .<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=125780177|title=Hypernova: An Iranian Rock Band In Brooklyn|website=npr.org|accessdate=26 December 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170316162407/http://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=125780177|archivedate=16 March 2017}}</ref>\n\n== Early life and musical career ==\nKodi Najm was born in [[Tehran|Tehran, Iran]]. He left Iran when he was 17 years old and moved to the [[New York City]] where he currently resides. He has written and released 4 Ep's (Universal, Fairy Tales (''single''), Exit Strategy)  and one full-length album [[Through the Chaos]] as a member of Hypernova.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=11182793|title=Hypernova: Illegal Indie-Rock from Iran|website=npr.org|accessdate=26 December 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303183310/http://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=11182793|archivedate=3 March 2016}}</ref> Najm has also recorded and composed a heavily electronic and orchestral concept album for the motion picture ''Koyakatsi'' in early 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/jason-silva/koyakatsi-film_b_1965107.html|title=Koyakatsi : Enter the Civilization of Light With Director Ayoub Qanir|first=Jason|last=Silva|date=18 October 2012|website=huffingtonpost.com|accessdate=26 December 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160318051149/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/jason-silva/koyakatsi-film_b_1965107.html|archivedate=18 March 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Solo work==\nCorrespondant Compilation 07\n<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.residentadvisor.net/